						<summary>

						<p>Fragmentary stone lying near the Kalamēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Vikramāditya VI (undated).</p>						

						<p>This undated fragmentary inscription refers to the reign of Tribhuvanamalla ruling from Kalyana. Only the <hi rend="italic">praśasti</hi> of the king is preserved. On palaeographic grounds the record would appear to be of the time of Vikramāditya VI.</p>						

